%S A396888 12,48,56,80,440,992,4048,16256,34592,48032,158080,282256,291584,
%T A396888 403216,867328,1566448,3283232,5982752,8380832,9322112,13910432,
%U A396888 18727168,48107552,64411232,67100672,70479376,81823040,105390752,117288032,406224064,516034048,694526432
%N A396888 Even integers whose ratio of the sum of their nontrivial even divisors to the sum of their nontrivial odd divisors is itself a divisor.
%C A396888 A139256 is a subset of this sequence.
%H A396888 Paolo P. Lava, <a href="/A396888/b396888.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..49</a>
%H A396888 Paolo P. Lava, <a href="/A396888/a396888.pdf">List of terms, sums and ratio</a>
%e A396888 Nontrivial divisors of 12 are 2, 3, 4, 6: sum of the even ones is 2 + 4 + 6 = 12, sum of the odd ones is 3 and 12/3 = 4 that is a divisor.
%e A396888 Nontrivial divisors of 440 are 2, 4, 5, 8, 10, 11, 20, 22, 40, 44, 55, 88, 110, 220: (2 + 4 + 8 + 10 + 20 + 22 + 40 + 44 + 88 + 110 + 220) / (5 + 11 + 55) = 568/71 = 8 that is a divisor.
%o A396888 (PARI) is(n) = if(n%2!=0,return(0)); my(v=valuation(n, 2), odd=n>>v, sOdd=sigma(odd), sEven=sOdd*(2^(v+1)-2)-n); sOdd--; if(sOdd==0, return(0)); q = sEven / sOdd; if(denominator(q)!=1, return(0)); n%q==0 \\ _David A. Corneth_, Jun 10 2026
%Y A396888 Cf. A048050, A139256.
%K A396888 nonn,hard,new
%O A396888 1,1
